The paper deals with the issue of privacy preservation in sensory data recovery, which is a topic related to cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves compressive sensing, which is a technique used in machine learning and signal processing (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of multiple environmental attributes to improve recovery accuracy, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) or databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves simulations and data analysis, which could be categorized under social and information networks (cs.SI).
